Second, for cash payments to acquire property, plant and equipment, this would typically appear in the Cash Flow Statement under investing activities. Looking at the Cash Flow Statement, I can see:
- Purchase of Fixed Assets: 0.00

The first value is 319828.12 (Selling Expenses from the Income Statement).
The second value is 0.00 (Purchase of Fixed Assets from the Cash Flow Statement).
